---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'June 4, 2025';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — opsbash.com"
  description="Privacy policy for opsbash.com. Learn how we use Google Analytics, Google AdSense, and how we protect your data."
  canonicalURL="https://opsbash.com/privacy-policy"
>
<main class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">

  <div class="mb-10">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-5">

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        OpsBash ("we", "us", or "our") operates the website at opsbash.com. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have. By using opsbash.com, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Tool inputs — we collect nothing</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        All tools on opsbash.com run entirely in your browser. Any input you enter — such as a cron expression — is processed locally and is never transmitted to our servers. We do not store, log, or have access to the data you enter into any tool.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Google Analytics</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        We use <strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Google Analytics</strong> to collect anonymous usage data about how visitors use opsbash.com. This includes information such as pages visited, time spent on pages, general geographic region (country/city level), device type, and browser type. This data helps us understand what tools are most useful and how to improve the site.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Google Analytics uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect this information. The data collected by Google Analytics is aggregated and does not personally identify you. Google may process this data on servers located outside your country.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        Google's use of analytics data is governed by the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Google AdSense</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        opsbash.com uses <strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Google AdSense</strong> to display advertisements. Google AdSense uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to opsbash.com and other websites across the internet.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you based on your visit to opsbash.com and/or other sites on the internet. You may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Google Ads Settings</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        For more information about how Google uses data when you use our site, visit <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">How Google uses data from sites that use Google services</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Cookies</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        opsbash.com uses the following types of cookies:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Functional cookies</strong> — We use <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">localStorage</code> to remember your dark/light mode preference. This data stays in your browser and is never sent to us.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Analytics cookies</strong> — Google Analytics uses cookies to collect anonymous usage statistics as described above.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Advertising cookies</strong> — Google AdSense uses cookies to personalise the ads you see as described above.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">We do not sell your data</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        OpsBash does not sell, rent, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to any third party for commercial purposes. The only data shared with third parties is the anonymous analytics data processed by Google Analytics and the advertising data processed by Google AdSense, both described above, and solely for the purposes of operating those services.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Opting out</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">You have several options to limit data collection:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Google Analytics opt-out:</strong> Install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a> to prevent Google Analytics from collecting data about your visits.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Personalised ads opt-out:</strong> Visit <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Google Ads Settings</a> or <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">aboutads.info</a> to opt out of personalised advertising.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-gray-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0"></span>
          <span><strong class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">Browser settings:</strong> You can configure your browser to block or delete cookies. Note that blocking all cookies may affect the functionality of some websites.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Third-party hosting</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        opsbash.com is hosted on third-party infrastructure (such as Netlify or Cloudflare). These platforms may automatically collect standard server logs including IP addresses, request timestamps, and user agent strings in accordance with their own privacy policies. We do not control this data and it is governed by those providers' terms.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        Depending on your location, you may have rights regarding your personal data including the right to access, correct, or delete data held about you. Because OpsBash does not directly collect or store personal data beyond what third-party services (Google Analytics, Google AdSense) process anonymously, requests should be directed to those services where applicable. For any other privacy questions, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@opsbash.com" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline font-mono">contact@opsbash.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised "last updated" date. Continued use of the site after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        Questions about this privacy policy? Email us at <a href="mailto:contact@opsbash.com" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline font-mono">contact@opsbash.com</a> or <a href="/contact" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline font-medium">use our contact page</a>. We respond within 48 hours.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</main>
</Layout>
